shared_text:
Troup Athletics
September 14 at 2:34 PM ·

The XC teams competed in the New Summerfield meet this weekend. For the varsity girls, 3 team members finished in the top 10 and received a medal: Marigold Hunter in 1st place followed by Meredith Howell in 3rd place and Danielle Puckett in 7th. Other team members were Alexa Splawn and Yanely Jaimes. The varsity girls team finished in 2nd place. The varsity boys team members were Josh Fort, Wade Gardner, Jamarion Lydia, Christian Howell, and Emanuel Gonzales.

In the middle school division, the MS girls placed 1st as a team! 5 team members placed top 10 and received a medal. Team members were Blair Bristor (1st), Madeline Howell (4th), Payton Wells (5th), Kambry Nelson (6th), Bailey Gibson (7th), and Audree Hinkle.
The MS boys placed 2nd as a team and had 2 team members place in the top 10 and receive a medal, Benny Bristor (7th) and Cason Nichols (10th). Other team members were Braxton Barton, Nathaniel Dowdy and Sean Flood.

post_text:
Troup Student Anglers had 3 teams compete in the THSBA Regional Fishing Tourney yesterday on Lake Tawakoni. 130 teams from the East & Northeast divisions qualified for Regionals. The three Troup teams were - Jordan LeBeff & Joseph Daily, Layne Boyer & Brayden Vess, and Jace Lovelady & Dalton Smith.

The tourney was a 3 fish limit and the top 54 teams qualified for the state tourney. Layne & Brayden finished with a 2 fish stringer of 8.48’ and Jace & Dalton finished in 7th place with a 3 fish stringer of 11.11’. This qualified both teams for the state fishing tourney on Lake Belton July 25-26.

Jace & Dalton also finished the regular fishing season as the 2nd place team (out of 139 teams) for the East Division in points for Angler of the Year.

The tourney was a 3 fish limit and the top 54 teams qualified for the state tourney. Layne & Brayden finished with a 2 fish stringer of 8.48’ and Jace & Dalton finished in 7th place with a 3 fish stringer of 11.11’. This qualified both teams for the state fishing tourney on Lake Belton July 25-26.

Troup Tiger Band Calendar 2020-21 (fall only).pdf

Troup Tiger Bands
May 23 at 1:26 PM ·

Troup HS Band Family!

Please see the calendar for the 2020-21 fall semester. The high school calendar is normally distributed much earlier; however, we are in a unique situation!

This calendar is a “best case” scenario, however we can fully expect to make a few modifications as we go! The band directors will continue to plan for a “normal” football season, playing in the stands, performing at half time, competing at UIL, pep rallies, etc. We will also plan for the numerous alternatives that may present themselves. Altered school calendar, modification to the football season, limited spectators, limited participants, health screenings, rehearsal procedures, extended breaks… the list could go on and on of potential hurdles!

Along with our school administration, decisions will be made to keep our students and families safe. Changes will be made well in advance, as best as we can, however some changes may happen without much notification. We just ask that we all remain flexible and positive.

The band directors can’t wait to get started with our students in late July! Have a great summer!

It is time to turn in your child’s school work that they have completed so far for the 3 weeks of assignments that have been sent home (Week of: March 23, March 30, and April 6) If you have been able to send completed work electronically to your child's teacher you do not have to turn the work in unless you would like to. Please keep the workbooks, but tear out the completed pages. Be sure your child’s first and last name is on each page. If your child has gotten behind just turn in what they have completed. You may turn in library books that you currently have at home. Our times for drop off are Friday from 4:00 pm - 6:00 pm and Saturday 10:00 am - 12:00 pm. Drop off will be at the front 3rd-5th grade building, at the parent pick up line. Please stay in your vehicle. We will come to you to collect the work. If you have any questions please contact your child’s teacher.

In compliance with Governor Abbot's order for schools to continue distance learning until May 4, Troup ISD campuses will remain closed. Troup ISD will continue to offer at-home learning opportunities and free student lunches during this time. We are following all recommended safety precautions at pick-up locations, and will continue to monitor and adjust as needed.

We realize that this is a difficult time for many. As a school district, our priority will always be the safety and security of our students, staff, and community as a whole.

Stay Safe.

post_text:
Troup ISD will be providing students lunches while our district is closed due to the COVID 19 Health Crisis.

Lunches will be available for pick-up only from 11:00 - 12:30 at the Troup Elementary Cafeteria beginning Tuesday, March 17.

District officials will also be transporting lunches to 4 locations for pick up. Students may pick up lunches at the following locations starting at 11:30 on Tuesday. The areas in town where students may pick up lunches are:

Troup Town Homes on Magnolia and Ponsard

Short Street Park

Alton Ashby City Park

Corner of Beulah and Paschal Street

What we do know is that there will likely be another opportunity for your kids to show their HLSR and Rodeo Austin projects, so IF you are interested in these opportunities, dont sell/process your animals just yet. We will do our best to relay information as it comes to us.

Track and Field results from Jack Frye Relays in Winona are attached. Varsity girls finished 7th out of 13 teams at their first meet of the season.

Notable marks/finishes (girls)
-Sophomore Marigold Hunter won both the 3200 and 1600
-Senior Hadley Derrick won her heat of the 400 placing third overall and was 8th in the 200
-Brooklyn Bednarz placed 8th in triple jump
-Reagan Shofner placed 5th in shot put
-Danielle Puckett placed 6th in the 3200
-Sophomore Jaycee Berryhill was 4th in discus
-Freshman Meredith Howell was 7th in the 3200 and 8th in the 1600

Track and Field results form Jack Frye Relays in Winona Boys

-Freshman Jake Bender won the 3200 and placed 6th in the 1600 in the JV division
-Senior Desmon Deason placed third overall in varsity boys triple jump

Our girls played two very tough games tonight. Coming away today with a tie against Canton and a loss against Prairieland. Despite the one bad defensive inning in our game against Prairieland, our girls made some strides and are getting better. The only way to get better is to play better teams and we did just that this weekend. I am and will always be proud of my girls when they give 100% and never give up! Troup Lady Tigers finished the weekend 3-1–1. Keep working hard girls, don’t ever settle, always want more! #alwayshungry #neversatisfied

Troup Athletics
February 24 at 12:01 PM ·

The Troup Lady Tigers hosted Brownsboro in their first home game of the season tonight. The Lady Tigers came from behind in the 6th inning to tie the game up 1-1. Going into extra innings for a second time this week, the Lady Tigers took the win in the bottom of the 8th inning with a walk of, by Jessie Minnix, that allowed for Lindsay Davis to score the winning run. The Lady Tigers did a much better job tonight putting the ball into play and taking care of business in the batters box. Lindsay Davis picked up her first win of the season, throwing the complete 8 inning game, while walking 1 batter, giving up just 1 hit, no earned runs and sending 17 back to the dugout with strike outs. I wouldn't be doing the team justice if I gave credit to just a few players, because it was a complete team effort. The loud and rowdy crew in our dugout kept our spirits up and the game alive! The Lady Tigers are now 1-1 on the season. Troup is set to host Eustace on Monday with a 6PM game start. Come on out and support our girls. They are so much fun to watch!
Coach Weeks
